&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unless there are other reasons for RV enlargement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exception: acute PR.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifies a CMR-derived PR fraction &amp;gt; 40%.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Steep deceleration is not specific for severe PR.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Not reliable in the presence of high RV end diastolic pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Defined as the duration of the PR signal divided by the total duration of diastole, with this cutoff identifying a CMR-derived PR fraction &amp;gt; 25%.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cutoff values for regurgitant volume and fraction are not well validated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RF data primarily derived from CMR with limited application with echocardiography.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
